<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="553" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,926,1167]" pageId="4" pageNumber="553">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,926,951]" pageId="4" pageNumber="553">Diagnosis</emphasis>
(male). General body color brown, transverse setal ctenidia of hind tibia not reaching its anterior face. These characteristics differentiate this species from 
<taxonomicName box="[729,899,963,987]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Hirotophora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="553" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="multiseriata">
<emphasis box="[729,899,963,987]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="553">H. multiseriata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ament" authorityYear="2018" box="[952,1084,963,987]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Hirotophora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="553" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chilensis">
<emphasis box="[952,1084,963,987]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="553">H. chilensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, respectively. Clear differences to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ament" authorityYear="2018" baseAuthorityName="Nakayama" baseAuthorityYear="2018" box="[182,303,998,1022]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Hirotophora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="553" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dividua">
<emphasis box="[182,303,998,1022]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="553">H. dividua</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
will probably be only found with SEMs of the phallus of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Beyer" authorityYear="1958" box="[985,1187,998,1022]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Chaetopleurophora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="553" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavimarginata">
<emphasis box="[985,1187,998,1022]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="553">H. flavimarginata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and/or the finding of female specimens of this species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
